s (180°C) until golden on top. Serve warm; best enjoyed with custard."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Make homemade custard in the Thermomix while the crumble is cooking in the oven.","If pears are not ripe then cook for up to 15 minutes longer in step 5.","The classic crumble is one of those easy puddings to make when you have fruit that needs using up, because you will almost certainly already have the crumble topping ingredients! Here we’ve added oats and nuts for an extra crunch. A beautifully comforting dessert when served hot with custard.","Use Bramley apples and fresh blackberries instead of pears and blueberries."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","45m","6 portions"]}